event.data: { "_id": "_Person_leila-negra", "type": "Person", "label": "Leila Negra", "description": "Leila Negra, the stage name of Marie Nejar (born March 20, 1930), is an Afro-German singer and actress. She began her career as a child film actor in the 1940s, became a singer after World War II, and left performing in the late 1950s to become a nurse.\nShe was born Marie Nejar in Mülheim an der Ruhr, Germany.[1] Her father was a black sailor out of Liverpool, England, who originally came from Ghana; he saw his daughter only a few times.[2] Her mother, Cécilie, was the daughter of a white German woman and a creole man from the island of Martinique", "authorityURIs": [ "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leila_Negra" ], "additionalTags": [], "created": "2021-01-23T22:15:43.208866+00:00", "createdBy": "abasaran" }

event.data: { "_id": "_Topic_birth-controll", "type": "Topic", "label": "Birth control", "description": "Birth control, also known as contraception and fertility control, is a method or device used to prevent pregnancy. Birth control has been used since ancient times, but effective and safe methods of birth control only became available in the 20th century. Planning, making available, and using birth control is called family planning. Some cultures limit or discourage access to birth control because they consider it to be morally, religiously, or politically undesirable.", "authorityURIs": [ "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Birth_control" ], "additionalTags": [], "created": "2021-01-23T20:27:51.239809+00:00", "createdBy": "abasaran" }

event.data: { "_id": "_Repertoire_12-tone-music", "type": "Repertoire", "label": "12-tone Music", "description": "(Britannica:)\"12-tone music, large body of music, written roughly since World War I, that uses the so-called 12-tone method or technique of composition. The Austrian-born composer Arnold Schoenberg is credited with the invention of this technique, although other composers (e.g., the American composer Charles Ives and the Austrian Josef Hauer) anticipated Schoenberg’s invention by writing music that in a few respects was similar technically to his 12-tone music.\"", "authorityURIs": [ "https://www.britannica.com/art/12-tone-music" ], "additionalTags": [], "created": "2021-01-29T15:24:47.094179+00:00", "createdBy": "eberner" }

event.data: { "_id": "_Topic_fandom", "type": "Topic", "label": "Fandom", "description": "A fandom is a subculture composed of fans characterized by a feeling of empathy and camaraderie with others who share a common interest. Fans typically are interested in even minor details of the objects of their fandom and spend a significant portion of their time and energy involved with their interest, often as a part of a social network with particular practices (a fandom); this is what differentiates \"fannish\" (fandom-affiliated) fans from those with only a casual interest.", "authorityURIs": [ "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fandom" ], "additionalTags": [ "_TCulturalStudies" ], "created": "2021-01-31T21:39:31.685087+00:00", "createdBy": "abasaran" }

{ "_id": "", "type": "Annotation", "clip": "_Clip_747b2f15-b05e-46a0-9232-a125af7b20c3", "relation": "RQuote", "target": "_Person_hermann-aicher", "quotes": "\"[...] anlässlich dieser Musikfestspiele hat sich auch die Town Hall, die doch einer der ältesten Konzertsäle New Yorks ist, ganz verändert. Es wurde extra mein Bühnenbildner, der Günther Schneider-Siemssen, von Wien nach New York beordert, um die Town Hall auszuschmücken, auf österreichisch-salzburgerischere Art. Also wenn Sie jetzt in die Town Hall gekommen sind in den drei Wochen war die Town Hall fast nicht wiederzuerkennen. Schon im Vestibül waren Salzburger Bilder, waren stimmungsvolle Aufnahmen mit den Marionetten am Salzburger Domplatz, am Kapitelplatz. Es war alles in den österreichischen Farben mit Blumen oder mit Girlanden geschmückt. Im Saal selbst waren große Gobelins aufgehängt über Fantasien über die Zauberflöte und so weiter. Die Bühne selbst in ein Blumenmeer getaucht in rot-weiß-roten Farben. Also man kam schon in die Town Hall herein, um ein Festspiel zu genießen.“", "date": "", "role": "", "instrument": "", "metaDate": "", "timecodeStart": 118, "timecodeEnd": 172, "confidence": "", "attribution": "", "comment": "", "fromPlatformMetadata": false, "interpretative": false, "constitutedBy": [], "refersTo": "" }
